The paper discusses interference management in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer engineering (cs.CE). Given the focus on interference management and spectral efficiency, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of precoding and scheduling also suggests cs.SI as a likely sub-category. The mention of wireless standards such as 5G and the potential impact on network architecture and design could also fall under cs.MM and cs.CE.
